title: Bruce Lee in Chinese Connection
description:
Bruce Lee consolidated his position as the cinema's greatest martial artist in this kung fu classic from Lo Wei, who also directed Lee's first starring vehicle Fists Of Fury, and several Jackie Chan
films.The legendary star is at his powerful, graceful best in this film ( also known as the Iron Hand), which is set in the early 1900's, and pulls no punches as the star pupil of Shanghai's
Chinese Karate School
